CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 1, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Awarded $25,000 - Mr.s and Mrs. Gerald Horsley, of Homewood, were awarded Federal jury verdicts totalling $25,000, to be paid by a Minnesota woman mortician, for damages caused by injuries which the Horsleys received in an automobile accident at Penn and Homewood Aves., July 3, 1955. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Helen Horsley, and Gerald Horsley wearing shirt with stripes and eyeglasses, seated in living room of their home at 7445 Hermitage Street, Homewood
